## v1.5.0 (2026-06-20)

**Changed by:** ProjectMnemosyne issue #309 R1 re-planning (iteration 2 of the planning issue)
**Verification:** verified-local for the required-context ENUMERATION technique (the
`jq … required_status_checks[].context` query WAS run and returned the eight pinned contexts);
**unverified** for the proposed guard placement (planning only — never implemented or CI-run).

### What changed

- Added **Section J: Place a merge-blocking guard in a PINNED required context** — the inverse of
  Sections A/G. A guard added to a job that is NOT a pinned required status-check context runs,
  goes green, and blocks nothing; a regression still "merges clean" (green-but-non-blocking
  security-theater). Captures the enumerate-then-verify discipline.
- Added a When-to-Use trigger (10): placing a merge-blocking guard and confirming its job is a
  pinned required context.
- Added a description trigger (10) mirroring the When-to-Use addition.
- Added Quick Reference item 5: the `jq` required-context enumeration one-liner plus a `grep -qx`
  two-sided placement guard that proves the target job BLOCKS (not merely that the step parses).
- Added a Failed Attempts row: placing the drift guard in `ci.yml`'s `validate` job (a NON-required
  job) → green-but-non-blocking; reviewer NOGO; fix = move into `_required.yml`'s `schema-validation`
  (pinned) job.
- Added a Results & Parameters subsection (the enumerated 8 contexts; R0 NOGO → R1 fixed placement;
  unverified reliances recorded as risks).
- Added a Verified On row for ProjectMnemosyne issue #309 R1.
- Added tags: pinned-context, merge-blocking, green-but-non-blocking.
- Bumped Overview Date/Objective/Outcome/Verification to reflect ten concerns and the partly-
  unverified Section J.

### Why

The R0 plan for issue #309 placed a new enforcement-drift guard in `ci.yml`'s `validate` job — the
most obvious config-validation job. A reviewer NOGO'd it: `validate` is not a pinned required
status-check context, so the guard would be advisory and a regression could still merge clean. R1
re-planning enumerated the ruleset's required contexts with `jq` (returning `lint, unit-tests,
integration-tests, security/dependency-scan, security/secrets-scan, build, schema-validation,
deps/version-sync`), confirmed each maps to a job `name:` in the canonical `_required.yml`, and moved
the guard into the pinned `schema-validation` job (which already loops the same four ruleset files).
Generalizable lesson: before placing any merge-blocking guard, enumerate the repo's
required-status-check contexts and confirm the target JOB NAME is in that set — the job `name:`, not
the workflow filename, is the pinned context. This is the inverse of the
`ci-driver-blocked-required-context-drift` / Section A/G hazard (deleting/renaming a pinned context
bricks the merge queue), and a sibling to `config-governance-fix-scope-all-variant-files` (the other
issue-#309 planning-discipline skill).

