Add RESULTS-loop aggregator gate pattern and guard test (planning phase, unverified)

- Added new "When to Use" bullet for the RESULTS-loop compact form.
- Added subsection E: RESULTS-loop aggregator gate — the `>-` block scalar that builds
  a space-separated `job=result` string iterated by a bash loop. Scales better than one
  env var per job for large `needs:` lists.
- Documented `skipped` vs `cancelled` semantics: GitHub emits `skipped` (not `cancelled`)
  when a job's `if:` condition is false; the bash loop accepts `skipped` as passing.
- Added guard test pattern: `test_all_required_jobs_wired_to_gate` asserts
  `gate.needs == all_jobs - excluded`, preventing silent bypass of branch protection
  when new jobs are added to the workflow.
- Added exclusion category table: regular CI jobs vs advisory vs self-required-context vs
  the gate itself.
- Added Failed Attempts row: `needs.*.result` wildcard in `if:` expressions is rejected
  at parse time — must list jobs individually or use the RESULTS bash loop.
